Sample T2D-GWAS Data

T2DGWAS.Rd

Genome-wide association study (GWAS) of T2D in Finnish population

Usage

data(T2DGWAS)

Format

Details

The 'T2DGWAS' contains association p-values for SNPs from from dbGaP (Analysis ID: pha002839). There are total 306,368 SNPs with their p-values available.

The data also comes with data frames of "snpGeneMap", "snpGeneP", "snpMap" and "T2DGWASGene"

"snpMap" is the map positions based on GRCh37, generated by the snpGeneSets function of getSNPMap().

"snpGeneMap" is the mapping of SNP to gene, generated by the snpGeneSets function of snp2Gene().

"snpGeneP" is similar to the "snpGeneMap", but it has an additional column of GWAS p-values for the SNPs

"T2DGWASGene" is the uniform score for T2DGWAS gene measures of minP, 2ndP, simP and fishP. It is generated by the function of getGeneMeasure().

Source

References

Scott LJ, Mohlke KL, Bonnycastle LL, Willer CJ, Li Y, Duren WL, Erdos MR, Stringham HM, Chines PS, Jackson AU et al: A genome-wide association study of type 2 diabetes in Finns detects multiple susceptibility variants. Science 2007, 316(5829):1341-1345.
